    "note": "Approved. 50 vocab + 66 grammar (comparatives 24, superlatives 21, as…as 21), the animals/comparison unit. Grants: as / better / worse / worst (SB box) + item-scoped \"mosquitoes\" (standard irregular plural the regular family misses). Smoke-check (pre-verify) fixed: variant-answer demotions (US centimeter, \"human being\", tonne, lorry → partial), farmer def off \"farm\", 3 group-sort labels reworded off grammar-meta (\"-er\"/\"-est\"/\"equal\" → exemplar labels), 1 chip-budget overflow. Verify round 1 caught two FALSE comparison facts (pigeon>ostrich at running; ostrich=giraffe height — both corrected to true), a synonym distractor (powerful for strong), a pronoun-remap ambiguity, and \"past\" masked by the name \"Past\" in w.ago — all fixed; round 2 clean. Stage-8: all 30 glosses correct German + genuinely above level, all 56 translations accurate. NOTE FOR KOKI: this unit is gloss-heavy (~40 glossed tokens) because the animal-category vocabulary — animal, bird, snake, insect, reptile, sea — is untaught at g2-u04 yet unavoidable in an animals unit. Worth considering whether \"animal\"/\"bird\" belong in the core taught set; for now they're correctly glossed. rejectRate 0.0%."
